  "prompt": "What universities does Inteliquent recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Inteliquent, a telecommunications company, typically recruits new graduates from a range of universities with strong programs in fields relevant to their industry. While specific universities and majors can vary, Inteliquent generally looks for candidates from institutions known for their engineering, computer science, information technology, and business programs.\n\nSome universities that Inteliquent might recruit from include:\n- University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign\n- Purdue University\n- University of Michigan\n- Northwestern University\n- Georgia Institute of Technology\n- University of Texas at Austin\n- Stanford University\n- Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)\n\nThe majors they are likely interested in include:\n- Electrical Engineering\n- Computer Science\n- Information Technology\n- Network Engineering\n- Telecommunications\n- Business Administration\n- Data Science\n- Cybersecurity\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it is recommended to check Inteliquent\u2019s careers page or contact their HR department directly.",
